cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with polytopes and valid inequalities for an integer programming formulation of a graph coloring problem. 
- cs.GT (Graph Theory) is also likely as the Equitable Coloring Problem is a graph coloring problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper presents computational evidence for the efficacy of the proposed cutting-plane algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper deals with algorithmic and computational aspects of the problem.
